    RefIds:
    - rid: 7832858370711486535
      type: {class: MatchingItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 1
        pairs:
        - question:
          - A passenger in a car lurches forward when the car suddenly stops.
          - When a car suddenly stops, a passenger stumbles forward.
          correctAnswer: Law of Inertia
        - question:
          - A small child can throw a baseball faster than a heavy medicine ball
            because the ball is lighter.
          - A baseball is lighter than a huge medicine ball, so a young child can
            throw it faster.
          correctAnswer: Law of Acceleration
        - question:
          - Pushing against a wall results in the wall pushing back with equal force
            (you feel it in your hands).
          - You can feel it in your hands as the wall pushes back with equal power
            when you push against it.
          correctAnswer: Law of Interaction
        wrongAnswers:
        - Enter zero or more extra wrong choices.
    - rid: 7832858370711486536
      type: {class: MatchingItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 2
        pairs:
        - question:
          - This is a force directly applied to object.
          - This force is applied directly to the object.
          correctAnswer: Applied Force
        - question:
          - It is a force resulting from pulling.
          - It is a force produced through pulling.
          correctAnswer: Tension Force
        - question:
          - Is a force that is perpendicular to the surface an object is placed upon.
          - Occurs when an object is put on a surface that is perpendicular to it.
          correctAnswer: Normal Force
        - question:
          - Is the resistance that one surface or object encounters when moving another.
          - Is the resistance that an object or surface faces when being moved by
            another.
          correctAnswer: Friction Force
        - question:
          - Is force exerted by air.
          - The air generates force.
          correctAnswer: Air resistance
        - question:
          - Forces that two object exert at a distance.
          - Forces acting at a distance between two objects.
          correctAnswer: Noncontact Forces
        - question:
          - This is kind of force wherein the second force can be divided into electrical
            and magnetic forces.
          - The second force in this type of force can be separated into magnetic
            and electrical forces.
          correctAnswer: Electromagnetic Forces
        wrongAnswers: []
    - rid: 7832858371272736768
      type: {class: MultipleChoiceItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - This law states that objects remain in their current state unless acted
          upon by an outside or unbalanced force. Which of the following best describes
          this law?
        - This law implies that until an external or imbalanced force acts, the thing
          stays in its existing state. Which of the following best describes this
          law?
        - According to this law, unless moved upon by an outside or unbalanced force,
          the thing remains in its current state. Which of the following best describes
          this law?
        correctAnswer:
        - First Law of Motion
        wrongAnswers:
        - Second Law of Motion
        - Third Law of Motion
        - Fourth Law of Motion
        choiceCount: 4
    - rid: 7832858371272736769
      type: {class: MultipleChoiceItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - This law states that an object accelerates if an unbalanced net force is
          applied. Which of the following best describes this law?
        - This law implies that an object moves when an unbalanced net force is applied.
          Which of the following best describes this law?
        - This law indicates that when an unbalanced net force occurs to an object,
          it will accelerate. Which of the following best describes this law?
        correctAnswer:
        - Second Law of Motion
        wrongAnswers:
        - First Law of Motion
        - Third Law of Motion
        - Fourth Law of Motion
        choiceCount: 4
    - rid: 7832858371272736770
      type: {class: MultipleChoiceItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - This law implies that there is always an equal and opposing amount of force
          counteracting another force. Which of the following best describes this
          law?
        - This law says that an equal and opposite quantity of force counteracts
          another force. Which of the following best describes this law?
        - This law states that an equal and opposite amount of force opposes another
          force. Which of the following best describes this law?
        correctAnswer:
        - Third Law of Motion
        wrongAnswers:
        - First Law of Motion
        - Second Law of Motion
        - Fourth Law of Motion
        choiceCount: 4
    - rid: 7832858371272736771
      type: {class: MultipleChoiceItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - What type of law states that pushing an empty shopping cart causes it to
          speed quickly, while a full cart is more difficult to push due to its increased
          mass? Which of the following best describes this law?
        - What form of law states that pushing an empty shopping cart leads it to
          accelerate rapidly, while a full cart becomes more difficult to push due
          to the additional mass? Which of the following best describes this law?
        - What type of law states that pushing an empty shopping cart causes it to
          speed quickly, while a loaded cart becomes more difficult to push due to
          the increased mass? Which of the following best describes this law?
        correctAnswer:
        - Second Law of Motion
        wrongAnswers:
        - First Law of Motion
        - Third Law of Motion
        - Fourth Law of Motion
        choiceCount: 4
    - rid: 7832858371272736772
      type: {class: CategorizationItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 2
        categoryItems:
        - category: Contact Forces
          items:
          - Applied Force
          - Tension Force
          - Normal Force
          - Friction
          - Air Resistance
        - category: Noncontact Forces
          items:
          - Gravitational Force
          - Electromagnetic Force
          - Electric Force
          - Magnetic Force
    - rid: 7832858371272736773
      type: {class: FillInTheBlanksItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 1
        question:
        - Fill in the blanks with the correct term for each statement. __________
          this kind of force acting on the object are not balanced.  __________ this
          kind of force states that object remains at current state.  __________
          this is resistance of an object to change its state of motion.
        - Fill in the blanks with the correct term for each statement. __________
          this sort of forces operating on the item are not balanced. __________
          this type of force indicates that the thing continues in its existing state.
          __________ this refers to an object's resistance to changing its state
          of motion.
        correctAnswers:
        - Unbalanced Force
        - Balanced Force
        - Inertia
        wrongAnswers:
        - State of Rest
        - Force (N)
